This paper discusses a peer-to-peer system for preserving access to journals and archival information published on the web. The system involves a large number of independent web caches that cooperate to detect and repair damage to their content by voting in "opinion polls." The paper focuses on a novel protocol for voting in systems of this kind, which incorporates rate limitation and intrusion detection. This work involves distributed systems (cs.DC), security and privacy (cs.CR), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), digital libraries (cs.DL), and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
